<h1>‚ùì Help - Pahana Edu Bookshop</h1>

<p>Welcome to the Help section. This guide will help new users understand how to use the system effectively.</p>

<h2>1. Dashboard Overview</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Customers:</strong> View, add, edit, or remove customer details.</li>
    <li><strong>Users:</strong> Manage system user accounts.</li>
    <li><strong>Books:</strong> View and add books to the inventory.</li>
    <li><strong>Sales:</strong> Record sales, manage the cart, and print receipts.</li>
    <li><strong>Help:</strong> Access guidance and support.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Using the Sales Section</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Select a book from the dropdown or add a new book manually.</li>
    <li>Enter the quantity and click <strong>Add to Cart</strong>.</li>
    <li>The cart table will display all selected items with quantity, price, and total.</li>
    <li>To remove an item, click the <strong>Remove ‚ùå</strong> button.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Pay üí≥</strong> to view and print the receipt.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Managing Customers</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Customers</strong> section.</li>
    <li>Add new customers, edit existing details, or remove customers as needed.</li>
    <li>Use the search function to quickly find a customer by name or ID.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Managing Books</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Books</strong> section to add or edit books.</li>
    <li>Keep book prices and quantities updated for accurate sales records.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Tips for New Users</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Always log out after finishing your work to secure the system.</li>
    <li>Check your cart before printing a receipt to ensure all items are correct.</li>
    <li>Use search features to save time in Customers and Books sections.</li>
</ul>

